column3: Marginal Food Insecurity (individual level)
column4: U.S. Census Bureau, Current Population Survey, December Supplement.
column6: Marginally food insecure if household answers "yes" to 1 or more questions from the Core Food Security Model, Current Population Survey.  The person-weight is used in all years except 2007 and thus the food insecurity rates reflect the fraction of individuals food insecure.

column3: Food Insecurity (individual level)
column4: U.S. Census Bureau, Current Population Survey, December Supplement.
column6: Food insecure if household answers "yes" to 3 or more questions from the Core Food Security Model, Current Population Survey.  The person-weight is used in all years except 2007 and thus the food insecurity rates reflect the fraction of individuals food insecure.

column3: Very Low Food Security (individual level)
column4: U.S. Census Bureau, Current Population Survey, December Supplement.
column6: Very low food secure if household with children answers "yes" to 8 or more questions, or household without children answers "yes" to more than 6 questions from the Core Food Security Model, Current Population Survey.  The person-weight is used in all years except 2007 and thus the food insecurity rates reflect the fraction of individuals food insecure.

column3: Gross Domestic Product by State (Millions)

column6: Measured in millions of current dollars (all industry total)
